Where is he?

176
00:16:05,113 --> 00:16:06,310
Mi Reuk.

177
00:16:06,420 --> 00:16:09,743
You are no coward.

178
00:16:10,069 --> 00:16:13,799
You did lose you courage once,

179
00:16:13,910 --> 00:16:17,328
but you still kept
walking your path.

180
00:16:17,794 --> 00:16:20,447
I trust you.

181
00:16:20,555 --> 00:16:25,545
Indeed! The Mi Reuk
I know is not a coward.

182
00:16:25,663 --> 00:16:28,634
You will cross the river
and go past the border,

183
00:16:28,747 --> 00:16:31,182
and you finally will reach Europe.

184
00:16:31,301 --> 00:16:34,408
But, if I go...

185
00:16:34,501 --> 00:16:37,373
What... what
will happen to you?

186
00:16:37,495 --> 00:16:40,077
You needn't worry about me.

187
00:16:40,198 --> 00:16:44,536
I will quietly wait
for your safe return.

188
00:16:44,687 --> 00:16:46,683
Doesn't time fly?

189
00:16:46,808 --> 00:16:47,682
Mother!

190
00:16:47,795 --> 00:16:54,284
Should you not be able
to ever make it back here,

191
00:16:54,406 --> 00:16:57,480
you shan't fall into despair.

192
00:16:58,700 --> 00:17:02,695
Raising you as
my child all this time,

193
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:06,542
I have been blessed with happiness.

194
00:17:06,948 --> 00:17:10,944
You gave me the kind of joy...

195
00:17:11,085 --> 00:17:15,481
nothing else in the world
would be able to.

196
00:17:15,610 --> 00:17:22,735
Now, walk on your path.
Don't think of your mother.

197
00:17:24,327 --> 00:17:27,591
You must walk that path alone.

198
00:18:51,998 --> 00:18:54,526
Hurry up!

199
00:19:03,324 --> 00:19:05,992
Where is he?

200
00:19:48,053 --> 00:19:50,548
"Korean Provisional Government"

201
00:19:51,774 --> 00:19:53,542
<i>Mother.</i>

202
00:19:54,177 --> 00:19:57,098
<i>After safely reaching Shanghai,</i>

203
00:19:57,205 --> 00:20:02,029
<i>I applied for a Chinese
passport to get to Europe.</i>

204
00:20:03,216 --> 00:20:04,629
<i>While I was waiting,</i>

205
00:20:04,817 --> 00:20:12,866
{\a6}[*Ahn Joong Geun = Korean independence activist
who killed Ito Hirobumi, Japan's PM]

206
00:20:04,817 --> 00:20:09,142
<i>I met the cousin of Ahn
Joong Geun*, Ahn Bong Geun,</i>

207
00:20:09,248 --> 00:20:12,866
<i>and I'm helping him at
the Provisional Government.</i>

208
00:20:12,976 --> 00:20:19,169
<i>So don't you worry about me.
They say this place is safe.</i>

209
00:20:28,154 --> 00:20:32,022
<i>Mother. Finally,
I received my passport,</i>

210
00:20:32,147 --> 00:20:35,471
<i>and I started
my trip towards Europe.</i>

211
00:20:35,581 --> 00:20:39,420
<i>Bong Geun Hyungnim agreed to
join me, on his way to France,</i>

212
00:20:39,547 --> 00:20:42,132
<i>and we are sharing
this experience together.</i>

213
00:20:45,521 --> 00:20:48,672
<i>On this ship, not only Joseon students,</i>

214
00:20:48,783 --> 00:20:53,000
{\a6}[*Annam was used by foreign states
up to the mid 19th Century for Vietnamese*]

215
00:20:48,783 --> 00:20:52,291
<i>but also people
from China and Annam*.</i>

216
00:20:52,677 --> 00:20:57,164
<i>We talked about
our concerns and future projects,</i>

217
00:20:57,418 --> 00:21:01,180
<i>and even discussed about
European politics and culture.</i>

218
00:21:01,669 --> 00:21:06,669
<i>{\a6}[*Swiss writer Gottfried Keller's
"Der grune Heinrich" - The Green Henry*]</i>

219
00:21:03,817 --> 00:21:08,232
It's a good book for learning German.
It's written with simplicity and candor.

220
00:21:11,135 --> 00:21:13,476
You're too quiet.

221
00:21:13,598 --> 00:21:16,083
You must be spending
too much time thinking.

222
00:21:16,501 --> 00:21:18,663
<i>In Asia, silence
is considered a virtue,</i>

223
00:21:19,199 --> 00:21:21,276
but it's different in the west.

224
00:21:21,383 --> 00:21:24,334
They consider it
antisocial and haughty.

225
00:21:24,443 --> 00:21:27,921
Try to spend time and socialize
with people, talk with them.

226
00:21:36,594 --> 00:21:42,084
<i>Just as you told me,
I safely reached Europe.</i>

227
00:21:42,552 --> 00:21:44,536
<i>Thanks to Bong Geun Hyungnim,</i>

228
00:21:44,644 --> 00:21:49,644
{\a6}[*Benedictine Abbey in Bavaria]

229
00:21:44,644 --> 00:21:48,885
I found refuge at the
Munsterschwarzach Abbey* in Germany.

230
00:21:52,950 --> 00:21:57,200
<i>It was here that I started focusing
on my German language studies,</i>

231
00:21:57,312 --> 00:21:59,463
<i>and I'm rapidly progressing.</i>

232
